{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Du6mNNiWP5ZsZrFtUxQp1a","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"158598b2-99ad-4ad2-ab32-7b9804b6de2c","uuid":"fcda36fd-c87c-40ef-95c1-51a763ac8d50","timestamp":"2026-03-25T07:32:52.773Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"### Session 12 — harness-run (2026-03-25T11:29Z)\n\nStarting session. Scanning for actionable stories.\n\n**Result:** NO_WORK — identical to sessions 7-11. 14-4-observability-backend-choice is retry-exhausted (10/10) and flagged. 65/66 stories done (98.5%). 6th consecutive no-op session. No autonomous work possible.","newString":"### Session 12 — harness-run (2026-03-25T11:29Z)\n\nStarting session. Scanning for actionable stories.\n\n**Result:** NO_WORK — identical to sessions 7-11. 14-4-observability-backend-choice is retry-exhausted (10/10) and flagged. 65/66 stories done (98.5%). 6th consecutive no-op session. No autonomous work possible.\n\n### Session 13 — harness-run (2026-03-25T11:32Z)\n\nStarting session. Scanning for actionable stories.\n\n**Result:** NO_WORK — 7th consecutive no-op session. 14-4-observability-backend-choice remains retry-exhausted (10/10) and flagged. 65/66 stories done (98.5%). Ralph loop should have terminated after session 8.","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-25\n\n### 15-4-fix-ts-compilation-errors — create-story (2026-03-25T05:55Z)\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- Original story quoted ~40 errors; actual count is 106. Epic definition was stale.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- AC2 (\"type annotation changes only\") boundary between type-only and logic change can be blurry\n- 4 source files (not just test files) have errors, carrying higher risk\n- 106 errors is large scope for single story\n\n**Observations:**\n- All 5 ACs are cli-verifiable — fully automatable\n- Error count has been growing for 13+ sessions\n\n### 15-4-fix-ts-compilation-errors — dev-story (2026-03-25T06:13Z)\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- None — all 106 errors fixed across 20 files.\n\n**Borderline logic changes:**\n- `dimensions.ts`: Changed `g.message` → `g.description`, removed nonexistent `g.fix`. Prior code was broken at runtime (undefined properties).\n- `run.ts`: Changed `'in-review'` → `'review'` to match StoryStatus type. Other system parts (bash/yaml) may still use `'in-review'`.\n- `docker-setup.ts`: `opensearch` property not in HarnessState interface but code writes it. Used `as HarnessState` cast.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- `deps.test.ts`/`otlp.test.ts`: Explicit parameter typing for overloaded mock callbacks (vitest limitation with overloaded functions).\n- `scan-cache.test.ts`: Removed `hasBmalph`/`bmalpthFiles` fields that never existed on `DetectedArtifacts`.\n\n**Observations:**\n- 16 test files had type errors vs 4 source files — tests were the primary debt vector.\n\n### 15-4-fix-ts-compilation-errors — code-review (2026-03-25T06:25Z)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- MEDIUM: `src/commands/run.ts` — `'in-review'` was invalid StoryStatus (should be `'review'`). Runtime behavior change, not type-only.\n- MEDIUM: `src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` — `g.message` referenced non-existent property (correct: `g.description`). Produced `undefined` at runtime.\n- MEDIUM: `src/modules/infra/docker-setup.ts` — `opensearch` not in HarnessState interface, suppressed with `as HarnessState` cast.\n\n**Code quality issues NOT fixed:**\n- LOW: HarnessState missing `opensearch` field definition — tech debt for future story.\n- LOW: Several test files use double-casts (`as unknown as T`) for partial mocks.\n\n**Coverage:** 97.1% overall, all 156 files above 80% floor. No gaps.\n\n**Items sent back:** None. All fixes correct.\n\n### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — verify (2026-03-25T06:40Z)\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- Docker keychain locked in non-interactive ralph session — cannot pull images. All Docker-based verification blocked.\n- Observability stack (VictoriaMetrics, VictoriaLogs, etc.) cannot start without Docker image pulls.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- Added `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->` tag to story file since all 10 ACs are `cli-verifiable`. Verified via source code inspection, grep, build, and test runs instead of Docker containers.\n\n**Observations:**\n- All ACs genuinely verifiable without Docker — the story is about code structure, function existence, and test passing.\n\n### 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget — verify (2026-03-25T06:45Z)\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- Same Docker keychain blocker as 14-5.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- Same unit-testable tag approach. All 10 ACs verified via code inspection and test execution.\n\n**Observations:**\n- Both stories had been stuck at `verifying` across multiple sessions due to Docker infra issues.\n- Tagging cli-verifiable stories as unit-testable is the correct fix — these should never have required Docker.\n\n### 15-5-lint-rule-bare-exception-swallowing — create-story (2026-03-25T06:50Z)\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- None. Story file already existed from prior planning session.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- `patches/error-handling/` directory doesn't exist yet — needs to be created.\n- AC1 references code-review subagent integration but is tagged cli-verifiable — borderline.\n\n**Observations:**\n- Story was pre-created. Verification tags already present and correct.\n\n### 15-5-lint-rule-bare-exception-swallowing — dev-story (2026-03-25T06:55Z)\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- `src/lib/scanner.ts` listed in story but has no Semgrep integration — actual Semgrep logic lives in `src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts`.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- Semgrep test fixtures use annotation format but can only validate with semgrep installed. Vitest tests validate file existence/content only.\n\n**Code quality concerns:**\n- `no-bare-except-ellipsis` rule uses Semgrep `...` metavariable — matches ALL except bodies, not just literal Ellipsis. Correct per AC1 but name misleading.\n- Hook grep pattern `except Exception.*pass` is approximate — matches comments/strings too.\n\n**Observations:**\n- All 3799 tests pass. Zero regressions.\n\n### 15-5-lint-rule-bare-exception-swallowing — code-review (2026-03-25T07:02Z)\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- HIGH: Hook grep pattern `except Exception.*pass` never matches multiline Python syntax (AC2 was non-functional). Fixed with awk-based multiline detection.\n- HIGH: Semgrep `no-bare-except-ellipsis` rule was false positive generator — `...` is Semgrep wildcard, not Python Ellipsis. Fixed with `pattern-regex`.\n- MEDIUM: Hook only detected `pass` but not Python `...` pattern. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: AGENTS.md stale after `additionalRulesDirs` addition. Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues NOT fixed:**\n- Story lists `src/lib/scanner.ts` but change correctly went to `analyzer.ts` — story spec inaccuracy.\n\n**Coverage:** 97.11% overall, all 156 files above 80% floor.\n\n### Session 7 — harness-run (2026-03-25T11:15Z)\n\nStarting session. Scanning for actionable stories.\n\n### Session 8 — harness-run (2026-03-25T11:18Z)\n\nStarting session. Scanning for actionable stories.\n\n**Result:** NO_WORK — no actionable stories remain. Only 14-4-observability-backend-choice is non-done but flagged as retry-exhausted. Sprint is effectively complete at 65/66 stories (98.5%). Session was a no-op.\n\n### Session 9 — harness-run (2026-03-25T11:22Z)\n\nStarting session. Scanning for actionable stories.\n\n**Result:** NO_WORK — same state as sessions 7-8. 14-4-observability-backend-choice remains the only non-done story, flagged for skipping. 65/66 stories done (98.5%). Sprint effectively complete.\n\n### Session 10 — harness-run (2026-03-25T11:24Z)\n\nStarting session. Scanning for actionable stories.\n\n**Result:** NO_WORK — identical state to sessions 7-9. 14-4-observability-backend-choice still the only non-done story, still flagged for skipping (8 retries, flagged by ralph). 65/66 stories done (98.5%). Sprint effectively complete. Ralph should stop spawning new sessions — there is no work left that can be done autonomously.\n\n### Session 11 — harness-run (2026-03-25T11:27Z)\n\nStarting session. Scanning for actionable stories.\n\n**Result:** NO_WORK — same state as sessions 7-10. 14-4-observability-backend-choice remains the sole non-done story (9 retries, flagged). 65/66 stories done (98.5%). Sprint complete for autonomous execution. This is the 5th consecutive no-op session — ralph loop should terminate.\n\n### Session 12 — harness-run (2026-03-25T11:29Z)\n\nStarting session. Scanning for actionable stories.\n\n**Result:** NO_WORK — identical to sessions 7-11. 14-4-observability-backend-choice is retry-exhausted (10/10) and flagged. 65/66 stories done (98.5%). 6th consecutive no-op session. No autonomous work possible.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":143,"oldLines":3,"newStart":143,"newLines":9,"lines":[" Starting session. Scanning for actionable stories."," "," **Result:** NO_WORK — identical to sessions 7-11. 14-4-observability-backend-choice is retry-exhausted (10/10) and flagged. 65/66 stories done (98.5%). 6th consecutive no-op session. No autonomous work possible.","+","+### Session 13 — harness-run (2026-03-25T11:32Z)","+","+Starting session. Scanning for actionable stories.","+","+**Result:** NO_WORK — 7th consecutive no-op session. 14-4-observability-backend-choice remains retry-exhausted (10/10) and flagged. 65/66 stories done (98.5%). Ralph loop should have terminated after session 8."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
